const { Client, Intents } = require('discord.js');
const myIntents = new Intents(32767);

As some of you may or may not know,the shortcuts Intents.ALL, Intents.NON_PRIVILEGED, and Intents.PRIVILEGED have all been removed to discourage bad practices of enabling unused intents. This means you have to apply for individual ones or use numbers to represent the intents you are using! Basically the number I used here means use all intents!
Gateway Intents were introduced by Discord so bot developers can choose which events their bot receives based on which data it needs to function.
To specify which events you want your bot to receive, first think about which events your bot needs to operate. Then select the required intents and add them to your client constructor, as shown below.

full details here: https://discord.com/developers/docs/topics/gateway#privileged-intents

const bot = new Client({ intents: myIntents });



