Embeds are often used to neaten things and fit everything nicely and you will probably use it a lot at a certain point!
remember to put message or messageCreate (actually whatever you are using, you can name it burger or potato for whatever reason!) in front of .channel.send(unless you defined the channels!)
v12: channel.send('Hello!', { embed }); (phased out)
v13: channel.send({ content: 'Hello!', embeds: [embed] }); (latest and greatest)



======================================================
messageCreate.reply()
replies to the request


messageCreate.channel.send()
sends a message to the channel the request came from, without using the reply feature!



